<LP>
   CHELSEA, Mass. -- Town &amp; Country Corp. said it signed a
letter of intent with an investment banker to underwrite the
sale of 30% of its Thailand unit, Essex International Co.
   The underwriting, which is contingent on regulatory
approval, will generate net proceeds of $20 million, Town &amp;
Country said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Town &amp; Country, a jewelry concern, said the stock of Essex
International will be traded on the Stock Exchange of
Thailand once approval is gained.
</TEXT>
